sources.description:
Budding Young Teenagers Were the Bluebeard's Prey! 
A troubled teen with an undeserved criminal past is the suspect when young women start turning up around town dead and marked up with lipstick.

Original title: Teen-Age Strangler (1964)  AKA: Terror in the Night
Subtitles added on this video

Director: Ben Parker
Writer: Clark Davis
Stars: Bill Bloom, John Ensign, Rick Harris, Stacy Smith
Genres: Crime, Drama, Horror, Mystery, psychotronic film

0:00 A man named Mr. Slade visits a couple, Mr. and Mrs. Harley, to inquire about renting rooms in their house.
9:52 A pathologist named Mr. Slade rents a room in the Harley's house and expresses his need for a quiet place to study and conduct experiments.
15:09 A group of people prepare for a theater show while the city is on edge due to the Ripper murders.
25:09 Inspector Warwick of Scotland Yard visits Miss Bonner to inquire about a woman named Annie Rowley, who has become a victim of Jack the Ripper.
30:55 A discussion about the Ripper case and the nature of criminals.
36:18 A woman named Miss Bonner expresses her concern to Mr. Slade about him being alone too much and missing out on the delights of the world, including the enjoyment of a man's kiss.
42:43 A tour of the Black Museum at Scotland Yard with Chief Inspector Melville and Miss Bonner.
47:21 A discussion about Jack the Ripper's crimes and the possibility of another murder occurring soon.
57:54 The characters discuss their suspicions about Dr. Slade and his actions.
